                <p>HISTORY (established, opened, closed, etc.)</p>
                <p>Opened May 17, 1844. Temporarily evacuated in 1937 - actual effective date not
                    had.</p>
                <p>Consulate closed 12/7/41.</p>
                <p>REMARKS:</p>
                <p>PB MEMO NOS.</p>
                <p>DEPT.CONTACTS</p>
                <table>
                    <row role="label">
                        <cell>DATE</cell>
                        <cell>ACTION, COMMUNICATIONS, REMARKS, ETC.</cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>9/4/37</cell>
                        <cell>Temporarily evacuated - actual effective date not yet reported. See
                            tgm. from Ambassador, Nanking, Sept. 4, 1937.</cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>12/7/41</cell>
                        <cell>Consulate closed 12/7/41 U.S. time upon declaration of war on US by
                            Japan. Non-confidential records, archives and Govt. property ordered
                            stored locally. Also see extracts from despatch of 4/9/43 from Mr.
                            Altaffer, Antigua (125.135/18) filed under "Archives" in room ill.
                            Airgram 436 of 11/1/43 from Bern says Amoy archives appear
                            intact.</cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </div>
            <div corresp="#c5650f2">
                <head>Amoy, China</head>
                <p>Desp. from Manila. PI Govt. consid. opening CG at Amoy to investigate and issue
                    re-entry permits to Chinese at Amoy to return to PI. Will request use of US
                    Consulate at Amoy pending re-opening of American office there.</p>
                <p>Included in 1950 budget figures for possible opening but emergency in area
                    precludes cons. this time.</p>
                <p>3/30/50 - <unclear>Darpatik</unclear> 1560, London, 3/30/50-Phil. property to
                    remain stored,</p>
            </div>
